### **Step 1.3: Set Up MongoDB Database**

1. Go to https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas/register
2. Sign up (free, no credit card)
3. Choose **"Free"** tier (M0)
4. Click **"Create"**
5. Cloud provider: **AWS**, Region: Choose closest to you
6. Cluster name: Leave default or name it `keysystem`
7. Click **"Create Cluster"** (takes 1-3 minutes)

8. **Create Database User:**
   - On left sidebar, click **"Database Access"**
   - Click **"Add New Database User"**
   - Username: `admin`
   - Password: Click **"Autogenerate Secure Password"** â†’ **COPY THIS PASSWORD** (save it somewhere!)
   - Click **"Add User"**

9. **Allow Network Access:**
   - On left sidebar, click **"Network Access"**
   - Click **"Add IP Address"**
   - Click **"Allow Access from Anywhere"** (adds `0.0.0.0/0`)
   - Click **"Confirm"**

10. **Get Connection String:**
    - On left sidebar, click **"Database"** (or **"Clusters"**)
    - Click **"Connect"** button on your cluster
    - Click **"Connect your application"**
    - Copy the connection string (looks like):
```
      mongodb+srv://admin:<password>@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
```
    - **IMPORTANT:** Replace `<password>` with the password you copied earlier
    - **Save this complete connection string!**

